          <td bgcolor="" valign="top" width="1"><img src="/magination/gfx/trans_header1.gif" width="22" height="2" vspace="0" hspace="0" border="0"></td>
          <td bgcolor="" valign="top"><!-- #BeginEditable "Body" --> 
            <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td>
      <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
        <tr>
          <td>
            <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">
              <tr> 
                <td class="chpurple"><font class="h1font"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/swccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/articles/articles.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/articles/articles.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3"><tr><td><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Entomb-What to use it on<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(3.57)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=9542'>ryan "XxTHEONExX" metzler</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=9542&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> February 19, 2002</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> Entomb is a very useful card in any core deck.  I recommend 1 in any Core deck either to counter opposing spells or to allow you to use non-core spells.  Most regions have discards spells, spells in which it forces the opponent to discard a creature from play.  Any Dark twins deck should have 2 of these.  The card allows Core to use cards such as shockwave and thunderquake, both very useful.  There are many uses for entomb and here are some of them split up between regions. I suggest that if a core player uses entomb for allowing him/her to play out of region spells he/she should also include another entomb to make defensive versus other decks.<br>
<br>
Core:<br>
Usually used to allow core to use apposing spells.  Only played in core decks.<br>
Orothe:<br>
Used to take out such cards as Will of Orothe, Tidal Wave, and undertow.  That&#8217;s 3 spells and you may want too metagame your area to make sure you entomb the right spells. Typhoon is another card to be wary of.<br>
Cald:<br>
Syphon vortex is the only card I would think of entombing.  I haven&#39;t played against many cald decks so I don&#8217;t really know but after looking over the sets this is the only discarding spell I could think of.<br>
Arderial:<br>
Now we come to Arderial.  There are only 2 cards worth entombing here.  I think all people know them Cataclysm and Shockwave.  These two cards can be very annoying and in a lot of other decks besides Arderial so watch out.  Also I have seen some people playing Harror so be careful.<br>
Naroom:<br>
Defiantly Sawgrass.  It is the naroom&#39;s version of arderial&#39;s shockwave.  Another card is gilded cage.  It can be very bad when it is discarded or placed on one of your core creatures like gorath or core grag.<br>
Universal:<br>
Universal has a few cards that could be entombed but not really have to be.  Maybe um...NO! if you know a person plays it for sure.  Maybe beam of light, but I wouldn&#39;t suggest entombing any universal spells.  If you are playing someone who works at duel you might consider entombing PotC because they might pull it out on your DT and totally screw the game.<br>
Weave: <br>
I don&#8217;t know of any cards to entomb but I would watch out for thunderquakes and shockwaves. <br>
Underneath: <br>
The first thing that comes to my mind when I think underneath is thunderquake.  Those can be very destructive.  It is in many decks and can help give an upper hand on the person who uses it.  Gorgle&#39;s curse is another one to be careful of.  It can hurt you for quite a while.  Bottomless pit and impact are threats but not as bad as the others.<br>
<br>
Entomb is a great core card.  It increased core&#39;s chances of winning by a lot.  Entomb can either be an offensive card or a defensive card.  It helps the core player even out the playing field.  Usually after you defeat a players magi and the next magi is sorreah they Cataclysm.  With entomb it gives arderial a fair win.  In my opinion cataclysm is a very broken card.  After you defeat their magi they pull out a cataclysm and then warriors boots in a creature and kill your magi.  This is a common problem solved by entomb.  Learn to use it and play it and it will give you the game.  Thank you for reading my extensive look at the core spell Entomb.<br>
